I’m afraid I still can’t locate any entry with that phone number. It might have been saved under a different format (e.g., without the “+1,” with dashes or spaces, or even as a nickname instead of the number itself), or it could already have been deleted.

1. Open your contacts list and search for “334-4098” or just “4098.”  
2. If that doesn’t turn anything up, scan for any names you don’t recognize—sometimes a contact ends up under a nickname.  
3. Once you spot the exact contact entry, let me know the name (or copy-paste the unique ID if your address book shows one), and I can delete it right away.

If there’s anything else I can try, just let me know!
